        "trailText":"Injured Frankie Dettori misses out on brilliant victor",
        "headline":"Treve is an easy winner of the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe at Longchamp",
        "body":"<p>Treve was a brilliant winner of the Qatar Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe, easily winning Europe's premier race at Longchamp on Sunday.</p><p>But the result meant heartbreak for Frankie Dettori, who was due to ride the unbeaten filly until he suffered a season-ending injury last Wednesday at Nottingham.</p><p>With Dettori out, Thierry Jarnet stepped in for the ride and he never had a moment of worry as his mount kicked clear of Japanese star Orfevre, who finished runner-up for the second successive year, with Intello in third.</p><p>Head-Maarek said: \"I want to say thank you to Frankie Dettori as he rode an amazing race on her in the Prix Vermeille. I said to save her for today and he did. A big kiss and thank you to Frankie, I am sorry he is not here today. She won so well, the way she won was incredible. She got no cover and had to come on the outside the whole way.\"</p><p>Jockey Christophe Soumillon was pleased with the performance of the runner-up, but thought Treve was unstoppable on the day.</p><p>He said: \"This year he was feeling very well and I was confident. [But] with the weight [allowance] the older horses give to the three-year-olds it is quite difficult for them. We had a good run. I would have preferred to sit fifth or sixth with a stronger pace but I don't think Treve was beatable today.</p><p>\"It's not my decision [if Orfevere will return next year], it's for the team to discuss. It is always difficult to think a horse can come back as a six-year-old but we will see. I think he's a great champion but Treve was the top horse today.\"</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/419187433|2013-10-07T10:05:57Z|d84c1ac591479701f50eb4c54a0bddfb186d9891 -->",
